Obergefell wanted to be listed as the surviving spouse on Arthur’s death certificate, so that he could be buried alongside his partner in a family grave plot exclusive to the Arthur family’s direct descendants and their spouses. But Ohio law, in not recognizing same-sex marriages within the state, wouldn’t allow it.
